<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1529,1987]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">
Comments: The critical study of the 
<typeStatus box="[619,667,1853,1879]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">type</typeStatus>
specimen allowed me to correct the subgeneric assignment for this species, transferring it from 
<emphasis box="[465,484,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C</emphasis>
. (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ayala" authorityYear="2002" box="[506,624,1889,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Aphemisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[506,624,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">Aphemisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Ayala, R." box="[638,771,1889,1915]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref5695" refString="Ayala, R. (2002) Two new subgenera of bees in the genus Centris (Hymenoptera: Apidae). Scientific Papers, Natural History Museum The University of Kansas, 25, 1 - 8. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8484" type="journal article" year="2002">Ayala, 2002</bibRefCitation>
to 
<emphasis box="[806,825,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[847,1009,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">Melanocentris</emphasis>
) due the strong apical curvature of the mandible and the shape of the innermost tooth. Considering the distance between the lateral ocellus and the compound eye, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1901" box="[281,423,1961,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellata">
<emphasis box="[281,300,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[314,423,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">scutellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be related to 
<taxonomicName box="[679,832,1961,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boliviensis">
<emphasis box="[679,698,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[712,832,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">boliviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1899" box="[846,993,1961,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavilabris">
<emphasis box="[846,865,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[878,993,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">flavilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Friese, 1924" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1924" box="[1048,1285,1961,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis box="[1048,1067,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1080,1136,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">fulva</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H." box="[1143,1285,1961,1987]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" pagination="19 - 22" refId="ref6117" refString="Friese, H. (1924) Neue formen der Bienengattungen Centris - Epicharis. Konowia, 3, 19 - 22." type="journal article" year="1924">Friese, 1924</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
